{"id":1714375,"name":"Grogo Kaz'Gromhur","campaign_id":273567,"entry":"<span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">Grogo is a dwarf cleric who follows the god Ilmater<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">. He is kind and compassionate and believes in forgiveness and redemption, even for his enemies<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">. He believes in sharing burdens rather than drowning under them<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><div class=\"paragraph normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:0rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">.<\/span><\/div><div class=\"paragraph heading2 ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:0rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">Grogo's Faith<\/span><\/div><div class=\"paragraph normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:0rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">Grogo's faith in Ilmater is a central part of his character<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><\/div><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">. Grogo often clashes with Hene, who is driven by a thirst for revenge<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">. Grogo tries to persuade Hene to abandon her quest for vengeance, arguing that it will only poison her<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">. He eventually accepts that sometimes revenge is necessary, but it should be guided by justice<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">. Grogo believes that his faith will guide him<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><div class=\"paragraph normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:0rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">.<\/span><\/div><div class=\"paragraph heading2 ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:0rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">Grogo and the <\/span><span class=\"italic ng-star-inserted\">Globo Netherese<\/span><\/div><div class=\"paragraph normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:0rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">Grogo was the one who found the <\/span><span class=\"italic ng-star-inserted\">Globo Netherese<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">, an ancient artefact<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><\/div><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">. This led to his village being attacked and his sister Lidia being kidnapped<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">. He initially blames himself for what happened<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">, but Hene reassures him that his actions were not pointless<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><div class=\"paragraph normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:0rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">.<\/span><\/div><div class=\"paragraph normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:0rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">Grogo believes that he and the <\/span><span class=\"italic ng-star-inserted\">Globo<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"> are now linked. The <\/span><span class=\"italic ng-star-inserted\">Globo<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"> has started whispering to him, tempting him with promises of power and the ability to end suffering around the world<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><\/div><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">.  He knows that the <\/span><span class=\"italic ng-star-inserted\">Globo<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"> is an instrument of corruption and must be destroyed<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><div class=\"paragraph normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:0rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">.<\/span><\/div><div class=\"paragraph heading2 ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:0rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">Grogo\u2019s Abilities<\/span><\/div><div class=\"paragraph normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:0rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">Grogo is a skilled magic user, proficient in both telekinesis and teleportation magic<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><\/div><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">. He rides a giant boar, a gift from Ilmater, to help him fight the Black Spider's forces<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><div class=\"paragraph normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:0rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">.<\/span><\/div><div class=\"paragraph normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:0rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">Grogo also has a magical sword that is cursed<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><\/div><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">. He asks Bungo Dudo and Yilvina to remove the curse, but they refuse<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">. Hene later realises that she could have removed it all along<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><div class=\"paragraph normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:0rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">.<\/span><\/div><div class=\"paragraph heading2 ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:0rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">Grogo's Future<\/span><\/div><div class=\"paragraph normal ng-star-inserted\" style=\"padding-left:0rem;\"><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">At the end of the campaign, Grogo decides to travel to Thay, the home of the Cult of the Broken Chain, to learn more about the <\/span><span class=\"italic ng-star-inserted\">Globo Netherese<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"> and how to destroy it<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><\/div><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">. He believes that the <\/span><span class=\"italic ng-star-inserted\">Pergamene Netherese<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"> might help him<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">. The <\/span><span class=\"italic ng-star-inserted\">Pergamene Netherese<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"> are a set of ancient scrolls that contain the fundamental theory of magic<\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\"><\/span><span class=\"ng-star-inserted\">.<\/span>","age":null,"sex":null,"pronouns":null,"created_at":"2024-10-01T21:22:07.000000Z","updated_at":"2025-05-01T21:57:20.000000Z","location_id":1714715,"title":"Il Martoriato","family_id":null,"is_private":0,"is_personality_visible":1,"type":null,"is_dead":0,"race_id":null,"deleted_at":null,"is_personality_pinned":0,"is_appearance_pinned":0,"entity":{"id":6751878,"entity_id":1714375,"parent_id":null,"type_id":1,"name":"Grogo Kaz'Gromhur","type":"NPC","entry":"<span class=\"n